    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Oil Pressure (EOP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f2650211005" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK09/K09041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EOP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The EOP sensor, a variable capacitance sensor, detects engine oil pressure.</para>
        <para>The EOP signal is monitored by the ECM for operation of the instrument panel pressure gauge and optional
            EWPS.
        </para>
        <para>The EOP sensor is installed in the intake side of the crankcase below the fuel filter header.</para>
    </svcproc>
